4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, a municipality may only
6 enforce speed limits within the corporate limits of the
7 municipality.
8 This bill would extend municipal enforcement of
9 speed limits to the municipality's police jurisdiction.
10
11
12 A BILL
13 TO BE ENTITLED
14 AN ACT
15
16 Relating to speed limits; to amend Section 32-5A-171,
17 Code of Alabama 1975, to expand the authority of municipal law
18 enforcement officers to enforce speed limits within both the
19 corporate limits and police jurisdiction of the municipality.
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
21 Section 1. Section 32-5A-171, Code of Alabama 1975, is
22 amended to read as follows:
23 "§32-5A-171
24 Except when a special hazard exists that requires lower
25 speed for compliance with Section 32-5A-170, the limits
26 hereinafter specified or established as hereinafter authorized
27 shall be maximum lawful speeds, and no person shall drive a
28 vehicle at a speed in excess of the maximum limits.
