29 (1) No person shall operate a vehicle in excess of 30
30 miles per hour in any urban district.
31 (2)a. No person shall operate a motor vehicle in excess
32 of 35 miles per hour on any unpaved road. For purposes of this
33 chapter the term "unpaved road" shall mean any highway under
34 the jurisdiction of any county, the surface of which consists
35 of natural earth, mixed soil, stabilized soil, aggregate,
36 crushed sea shells, or similar materials without the use of
37 asphalt, cement, or similar binders.
38 b. No person shall operate a motor vehicle on any
39 county-maintained paved road in an unincorporated area of the
40 state at a speed in excess of 45 miles per hour unless a
41 different maximum speed is established under authority granted
42 in subdivision (6) or as provided in subdivision (7) subject
43 to the maximum rate of speed provided in subdivision (3).
44 (3) No person shall operate a motor vehicle on the
45 highways in this state, other than interstate highways or
46 highways having four or more traffic lanes, at a speed in
47 excess of 55 miles per hour at any time unless a different
48 maximum rate of speed is authorized by the Governor under
49 authority granted in subdivision (6) or as provided in
50 subdivision (7).
51 (4) No person shall operate a motor vehicle, on an
52 interstate highway within the State of Alabama, at a speed in
53 excess of 70 miles per hour or on any other highway having
54 four or more traffic lanes at a speed in excess of 65 miles
55 per hour, unless a different maximum rate of speed is
